urlText: T1 Western Line: Trackwork between Lidcombe and Strathfield
content:
Saturday 4 and Sunday 5 December

  • Buses replace trains between Lidcombe and Strathfield.
  • Trains run to a changed timetable between:
    • Penrith and Lindfield via the T3 Bankstown Line 
    • Penrith and Lidcombe, then Olympic Park
    • Richmond and Leppington via the T5 Cumberland Line
    • Lidcombe and the City via the T3 Bankstown Line
    • Strathfield and the City
  • If you are travelling to the City or T1 North Shore Line stations you can catch a direct train via Bankstown, or change at Lidcombe for a T3 Bankstown Line service.
  • Express buses also run between Blacktown and Central.
  • If you are travelling to Flemington, Homebush or Strathfield please change at Lidcombe for a bus.
    Trackwork buses do not leave from Olympic Park.

urlText: L2 Randwick Line and L3 Kingsford Line weekend partial closure
content:
From 5am Saturday 27 November to 1am Monday 29 November 2021, L2 Randwick Line and L3 Kingsford Line light rail services will not run between Circular Quay and Central Chalmers Street, due to essential planned maintenance works.

You can use alternative transport including nearby trains or walking.

Buses will continue to replace L1 Dulwich Hill Line light rail services as per normal schedule.

Normal L2 and L3 Lines full light rail services will resume at 5am Monday 29 November.

Please note, COVID-19 safe restrictions will still be in place for alternative transport such as trains or buses.
subtitle: L2 Randwick Line and L3 Kingsford Line weekend partial closure
